answers.answer: I love chemistry and anything that involves environmental science. I'm fascinated by how natural systems work and how we can engineer solutions for pollution and climate issues.

I want to work in sustainable infrastructure or clean tech. Maybe something like water systems for developing communities or eco-friendly city planning.

Hands-on labs, fieldwork, and being around people who care about the world.

answers.answer: I don’t mind science or math, but I really like learning how things work in the real world — like how stuff is built or how small businesses get started.
I help out with my uncle’s farm sometimes. I also like fixing stuff — bikes, motors, random tools — and coming up with ways to make side money.
I like when something’s broken and I have to figure out how to fix it or make it more efficient. I also like finding ways to make or save money with whatever I’ve got.
Running my own thing. Or working outside, doing something hands-on where I can see the results of what I did.
I want to build something useful or support my family. Maybe even hire people someday.
Tools and nature for sure. I like getting my hands dirty and figuring it out as I go.

careers.title: Entrepreneur
careers.description: Entrepreneurs create and manage their own businesses, using their skills and knowledge to develop new products or services, or to solve unique problems. This path requires creativity, leadership, and a strong understanding of business management.

careers.title: Software Engineer
careers.description: Software engineers design and create software systems. They may work on applications or systems software, and they often specialize in areas such as networking, databases, or cybersecurity. This career requires problem-solving skills, a strong understanding of computer systems, and the ability to work with complex information.

careers.title: Farm Manager
careers.description: Farm Managers oversee the operation and maintenance of farms. They make decisions about planting and harvesting crops, raising and feeding livestock, and managing farm finances.
